Option 1 (Recommended for most environments): Microsoft Entra Cloud Sync
A lightweight, modern sync agent managed mostly in the cloud.
✔ When to choose Cloud Sync

You want simpler maintenance (agent only)
You want better high availability
You want faster sync cycles

⭐ Microsoft Documentation confirms Cloud Sync setup is done in Entra Admin Center, and involves:

Creating a Cloud Sync configuration
Installing the Cloud Sync Agent on a domain‑joined server
 [learn.microsoft.com]


How to set up Cloud Sync (Step‑by‑Step)
➡️ Step 1 — Sign in to Microsoft Entra Admin Center

Go to entra.microsoft.com
Navigate: Identity → Entra Connect → Cloud Sync
Click New configuration
Choose: AD to Microsoft Entra ID sync [learn.microsoft.com]

➡️ Step 2 — Download and Install Cloud Sync Agent

Still under Cloud Sync, go to Agents
Click Download on‑premises agent
Accept terms and download the installer
Install it on a domain‑joined Windows Server 2016+
 [alitajran.com]


➡️ Step 3 — Configure Sync (in the cloud)
From the Cloud Sync configuration screen:

Select domain
Enable Password Hash Sync (recommended)
Configure the 5 sections:

Scoping filters (choose which OUs/users/groups sync)
Attribute mapping
Test configuration
Review defaults
Enable sync [learn.microsoft.com]

➡️ Step 4 — Enable Sync
Once you click Enable, sync automatically begins.

⏱️ How to force sync when using Cloud Sync
Cloud Sync sync logic occurs in the cloud — there is no local PowerShell command like Azure AD Connect.
Instead:

Go to Entra Admin Center → Entra Connect → Cloud Sync → Provisioning Logs
Use Restart provisioning or Retry from the cloud interface
(Cloud Sync does not have Start-ADSyncSyncCycle because the engine runs in Microsoft’s cloud).


✅ Option 2: Microsoft Entra Connect (formerly Azure AD Connect)
Heavier, but still widely used.
If you choose this route, you must install it first—you cannot force sync without it.
A step‑by‑step setup guide confirms installation is done via Entra Admin Center → Entra Connect → Download Connect Sync.
 [activedire...orypro.com], [experts-exchange.com]

When should you install Microsoft Entra Connect instead of Cloud Sync?
Choose Entra Connect if:

You need device writeback, group writeback, or other advanced features
You have Exchange hybrid (classic)



