Microsoft officially states that Azure AD Connect (now Entra Connect Sync) must be downloaded from the Microsoft Entra Admin Center, and installed on a domain‑joined Windows Server running Windows Server 2016 or later. [activedire...orypro.com]
Below is the full, correct installation workflow step‑by‑step.

🧩 1. Prerequisites (Must be ready before installation)
Microsoft documentation confirms these requirements:

A Microsoft Entra (Azure AD) tenant
A domain‑joined Windows Server 2016/2019/2022 to install Entra Connect Sync
A Global Administrator account in Microsoft 365
A Domain Administrator account in your on‑prem Active Directory
A routable UPN suffix in on‑prem AD (e.g., @example.com, not @local.local) [activedire...orypro.com]

If your AD uses .local, you must add your real domain (e.g., company.com) as a UPN suffix first (see Step 2 below).

🛠️ 2. Add Your Microsoft 365 Domain as a UPN Suffix in On‑Prem AD
To sync users successfully, your AD must have the same domain suffix as Microsoft 365 (example: @company.com).
This setup is required and confirmed in hybrid sync documentation. [experts-exchange.com]
Steps:

Open Active Directory Domains and Trusts
Right‑click Active Directory Domains and Trusts at the top
Select Properties
Add your Microsoft 365 domain (e.g., company.com)
Click Add → Apply

After this, convert your users’ UPNs to use the new domain.

💾 3. Download Azure AD Connect / Entra Connect Sync
Microsoft states the install file is only available via the Entra Admin Center. [activedire...orypro.com]
Steps:

Go to entra.microsoft.com
Navigate to:
Entra ID → Entra Connect → Connect Sync
Click Download the latest Entra Connect Sync version
Accept terms and download the .msi installer

This downloads the official AzureADConnect.msi.

🖥️ 4. Install Microsoft Entra Connect Sync
Steps confirmed by official setup documentation: [activedire...orypro.com]
Steps:

Run AzureADConnect.msi
Accept license terms
Choose Customize (recommended — more control)
On the Install required components screen → Click Install
On the User Sign‑in screen → Choose one:

Password Hash Synchronization (PHS) → Recommended for most
Pass‑through Authentication (PTA)


Click Next
Enter Microsoft 365 Global Admin credentials
Enter Domain Admin credentials for on‑prem AD
Select what OUs you want to sync
Uncheck:
✔ Start the synchronization process when configuration completes
(This lets you verify before syncing, recommended by experts) [experts-exchange.com]
Complete the setup wizard

Installation is done — sync engine is now installed.

🔄 5. Start the First Sync
Once installed, you can manually trigger the sync.
Run PowerShell as Administrator on the Entra Connect server:
🔄 Delta Sync (just changes)
PowerShellStart-ADSyncSyncCycle -PolicyType DeltaShow more lines
🔁 Full Sync (complete resync)
PowerShellStart-ADSyncSyncCycle -PolicyType InitialShow more lines
(Commands valid only after Entra Connect Sync is installed.)

🧪 6. Test With a Small OU First (Best practice)
Experts recommend creating a Test OU, moving a few accounts inside, and syncing only that OU before syncing your whole domain. [experts-exchange.com]
Steps:

Create an OU like: Test AD Sync
Move 1–3 test accounts into it
Sync only that OU in the Connect setup
Trigger a sync
Confirm users appear in Microsoft 365 / Entra ID → Users

Once everything works, add additional OUs.

🕵️ 7. Verify Sync Status
Microsoft documentation confirms you can check sync status through:
PowerShell
PowerShellGet-ADSyncSchedulerShow more lines
Portal
Go to:
Entra Admin Center → Entra Connect → Connect Sync

🎉 Your Azure AD Connect / Entra Connect Sync is Now Installed
You now have hybrid identity and directory sync running.


